data.name: ExpBtn.ToolTip
data.value: Expands precisely the specified number of levels, the number being specified in the control on the right-hand side of this button group. After clicking this button, all nodes of the level up to the specified one will be visible in the tree view, and all the nodes beyond dtat level will be invisible.

data.name: ExpMaxBtn.ToolTip
data.value: Collapses all nodes of level beyond the specified one, the level being specified by the control on the right-hand side of this button group. After clicking this button, all nodes of the level beyond the specified one will be hidden in the tree view. Nodes below this level that were hidden before will remain hidden.

data.name: ExpMinBtn.ToolTip
data.value: Expands at least the specified number of levels, the number being specified in the control on the right-hand side of this button group. After clicking this button, all nodes of the level up to the specified one will be visible in the tree view. Nodes above this level that were visible before will remain visible.

data.name: MenuTools_Controls.ToolTipText
data.value: Toggles the panel with control buttons. A check shows whether the panel is shown or hidden. Most of the panel functionality can be accessed through the context menu (right-click on nodes in the tree view).
